==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: no-hit
<hw>no-hit</hw> <fld>(Baseball)</fld> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Baseball)</fld> <def>having no hits; characterized by one team
scoring no hits; -- of a baseball game (or the pitching) in which a
pitcher allows the opponent no hits; <as>as, he pitched <ex>no-hit</ex>
ball for seven innings</as>. A no-hit game is usually referred to as a
<er>no-hitter</er>; <as>as, His <ex>no-hit</ex> pitching</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hitless.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <au>+PJC</au></p>

